Pensacola Golf at Cypess Lakes Golf Club
Play your next round at Cypress Lakes
Cypress Lakes Golf Club is a very scenic Pensacola golf course that is cut through Pine, Oak, and Magnolia Trees. Dozens of Bald & Leyland Cypress trees combined with over 300 Crepe Myrtles & 500 Azaleas throughout the golf course make it absolutely breath-taking during the spring. This is an uncharacteristic Florida golf course, as it has a somewhat mountainous terrain although there are less than a handful of blind shots.
Pensacola golf experience
The gentle undulation of this William Amick-designed course weaves a challenging yet pleasant golf experience, pleasing to our members year after year. Contact the Pro Shop to book your reservation today or request information about our Pensacola Golf Memberships.

Cypress Lakes Golf Membership – Pensacola Golf
Member benefits & rates
Fees and Dues
(All categories are family memberships except Junior membership)
Membership:
$110/month
Discount Membership (plant & military):
Ascend Retirees, Solutia Retirees, Monsanto Retirees, Exxon, NFCU, & Chemstrand employees, company retirees, on site contractors, military (active & retired with ID), disabled Vet with paperwork…
($95 per month*).
Current Ascend Employees:
($85 per month*)
*MONTHLY RATES AVAILABLE WITH CREDIT CARD ON FILE
(Above memberships allow you, your spouse, and any unmarried dependent children ages 24 & under who are not regularly employed to play golf at Cypress Lakes Golf Club without paying green fees).
Junior Executive Membership
for members under the age of 26.
$60/month* The discount is available until they reach 26.
Current Daily Rates include Green fee, cart fee, & tax
Monday-Friday $50
Saturday-Sunday $55
All Inclusive membership
$310/month (Individual)
$375/month (family)
This membership includes unlimited range balls and carts.
Please contact us if you have any questions
850-937-3820 or info@cypresslakesgolfclub.net
